        "client_msg_id": "a4c910b5-3a11-4279-9a4b-d3a34daba1b7",
        "text": "Thanks <@UCUSW7WVD>! This is very helpful.\n\nI recognize my goals as mostly a combination of the points listed, but there is one more aspect which is somewhat related to other points but also distinct: People (users, other developers, ...) have no chance of knowing precisely what a program does if they have not written it themselves. Put differently, expressing software source code is a form of encryption of the initial developers' intentions.\n\nAn obvious illustration is spyware, but the problem exists even in a world without evil-minded players. In my field of work, computational science, it has become impossible to understand someone else's work, because so much of it is documented only by source code.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
